      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your feelings of emptiness and loss are valid, but the idea that this version of you is \"gone\" is likely a symptom of depression rather than an absolute fact. Many people experience profound grief and dissociation like this, yet they find that a new, resilient self can emerge once they begin to heal. Instead of immediately trying to fill the void, you might consider speaking with a therapist who specializes in trauma or existential issues to help you reconnect with what truly matters to you.",
      "source": "target",
